HEADWORD: Inaquate
<hw>In*a"quate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inaquatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>inaquare</ets> to make into water;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>aqua</ets> water.]</ety> <def>Embodied
in, or changed into, water.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cranmer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inaquation</ent>⟦br⟧
